METHODOLOGY:
This bill authorizes the Department of Military Affairs and Veterans Services to lease or license
property under its jurisdiction, provides that property leased or licensed to non tax exempt
entitiesis subject tolocal propertytaxation,establishes lesseeresponsibilityfor payment of such
taxes, and creates a dedicated, nonlapsing Department of Military Affairs and Veterans Services
PropertyFund.
The Department of Military Affairs and Veterans Services states this bill would authorize the
Department to lease or license property and establish a dedicated, nonlapsing property fund to
receive revenues generated from such activity, but the amount of revenues received into that
fund is indeterminable. The Department states it does not currently lease or license property to
private entities and therefore does not have existing lease or license revenue that would
otherwise lapse to the General Fund. The Department states the creation of the property fund
would not reduce the need for General Fund appropriations. To implement this bill, the
Department requests one new full time position titled Property Manager. The Department
estimates the cost of this position at $105,000 in FY 2027, $107,000 in FY 2028, and $112,000 in
FY2029. Thebilldoesnotauthorizenorappropriatefundstosupportthisposition.

The Department states there is no direct fiscal impact on county or local expenditures; however,
municipalities may receive property tax revenue when department property is leased or licensed
tonontaxexemptentities,asprovidedinthebill.
